## Content and CMS

Full docs: [docs/cms/README.md](docs/cms/README.md) ¬∑ Contract: [docs/cms/sveltia-content-contract.md](docs/cms/sveltia-content-contract.md)

- **CMS editor:** `/admin` ‚Äî Sveltia CMS (configure `backend.repo` in `static/admin/config.yml`)
- **Content directory:** `content/` ‚Äî Git-backed YAML and Markdown files
- **Loaders:** `src/lib/content/` ‚Äî `loadHomePage()`, `loadArticle()`, `loadArticles()`, etc.
- **Types:** `src/lib/content/types.ts`
- **Schema:** `static/admin/config.yml` ‚Äî the definitive collection and field definitions

### Parser rules ‚Äî critical, do not mix

| File type | Parser | Notes |
|-----------|--------|-------|
| `content/pages/*.yml`, `content/team/*.yml`, `content/testimonials/*.yml` | **js-yaml** | Pure YAML, no `---` delimiters |
| `content/articles/*.md` | **gray-matter** | Remap `.content` ‚Üí `.body` explicitly |

- Never use gray-matter for pure YAML files
- Never use js-yaml for Markdown frontmatter files
- Always remap gray-matter body: `return { ...data, body: content }` ‚Äî never `data.body`
- File-reading routes must use `+page.server.ts`, not `+page.ts`

### Sveltia CMS gotchas

- Field names in `config.yml` = TypeScript properties = Svelte component data keys ‚Äî they are a contract
- Never rename a field without updating config, content files, types, loaders, components, and docs
- Use `snake_case` for all YAML field names
- Do not use `content` or `data` as field names ‚Äî they clash with loader conventions
- CMS image fields must render through `CmsImage`, not bare `<img>`
- `local_backend: true` in `config.yml` is for local dev only ‚Äî remove before deploying
- To add a collection: config + starter file + type + loader + route + SEO entry + docs (all 6 steps)

## Automation (n8n)

Full docs: [docs/automations/README.md](docs/automations/README.md)

n8n is an optional external automation layer. The site works without it.

- **Do not** add n8n to `package.json`
- **Do not** import n8n packages in any SvelteKit module
- **Content automations:** n8n writes to `content/` via GitHub API ‚Äî must follow `config.yml` schema
- **Runtime automations (Phase 5):** server action ‚Üí Postgres ‚Üí non-blocking webhook ‚Üí n8n
- Webhook code must check `N8N_WEBHOOK_URL` and skip silently if unset
- Webhook delivery failures must not break user-facing form submissions
- Production webhooks must be HMAC-signed with `N8N_WEBHOOK_SECRET`
- Do not commit real webhook URLs or secrets ‚Äî use `.env.example` for variable names only
- AI-generated content must default to `draft: true` / `published: false`

## Secrets and environment

This project uses **SOPS + age** for secrets management (template default ‚Äî see [docs/deployment/secrets.md](docs/deployment/secrets.md)).

- `secrets.yaml` ‚Äî encrypted source of truth; commit only after `sops --encrypt --in-place secrets.yaml`
- `.env.example` ‚Äî public contract for required variable names (no values)
- `.env` ‚Äî rendered local/runtime artifact; gitignored; never the source of truth
- `~/.config/sops/age/keys.txt` ‚Äî private age identity; never committed

Required env vars: see `.env.example`
Secrets workflow: `bun run secrets:render` / `bun run secrets:check`

### Secrets rules for agents

- Never commit `.env` or any `.env.*` file except `.env.example`.
- Never commit plaintext `secrets.yaml` (check for `sops:` block before staging).
- Never put real secret values in `src/lib/config/site.ts` or any module that can be imported by client-side code.
- Never import `DATABASE_URL`, `SESSION_SECRET`, or other private secrets into `+page.svelte` or client-accessible `src/lib/` files.
- Never add OpenBao, Doppler, Infisical, 1Password Secrets Automation, or cloud KMS integrations unless this project has explicitly changed this decision.
- When adding a new required environment variable, update `.env.example` and `secrets.example.yaml` together.

